<item>
            <title>[WICKET-4340] Rerendering a page with WicketTester after you loose permission does not give access-denied</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4340</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4256&quot; title=&quot;onBeforeRender() is called on components that are not allowed to render&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-4256&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-4256&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; WicketTester does not give an access-denied page when you try to rerender a page instance after loosing permission to render that page. A testcase is added to WicketTesterTest (rerenderNotAllowed) to demonstrate the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12538604">WICKET-4340</key>
            <summary>Rerendering a page with WicketTester after you loose permission does not give access-denied</summary>
